.ezboard.com/uatomicconspiracy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Atomic Conspiracy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/19/02 2:16:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=74.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.att.net/~foundation1/starnship.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Origin of my user name</span><hr size=1> A couple of years ago, when I first joined the Project Orion Club at Yahoo!, I used another, and basically innocuous name. <br>
The battle with the notorious ASTS mob was just heating up then and would eventually reach unprecedented levels of invective and slander before it ended in the total rout and destruction of the ASTSers and their allies, the SE Flyers  (aka SE Liars, Flying Monkeys, and Lying Monkeys). <br>
However, it was a very difficult fight for a while. One night, a flurry of especially vicious ASTS attacks accused us of being a terrorist front and a gang of evil conspirators plotting to take over the world and harm small animals or something. <br>
In response, I decided that a more bellicose and confrontational name might be in order, preferably one that would rub their stupid fantasies right in their faces. <br>
<br>
I happened to remember an old science fiction paperback I have in my collection, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The Atom Conspiracy</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> by Jeff Sutton. <br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://people.uncw.edu/smithms/Ace%20singles/sF-series/F-374.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Published in 1963, this is set in a future world where a druid-like priesthood rules with absolute power. It retains its power through, among other things, restrictions on scientific research, including a total ban on all forms of nuclear research. <br>
The protagonist is a druid agent who investigates a secret  attempt to revive nuclear research. He ends up joining this &quot;atom conspiracy&quot; himself, and helps overthrow the druid overlords and revive scientific progress. <br>
The name seemed ideal, except for the change from noun to pronoun, and I rejoined the club as &quot;atomic conspiracy&quot;. <br>
The use of &quot;atomic&quot; rather than &quot;nuclear&quot; evoked an earlier and more positive set of attitudes toward this energy, reflecting this group's long-standing goal of applying atomic energy to a peaceful revolution in human affairs, the exploration and settlement of outer space. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2230<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/10/02 10:37:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=74.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Democracy out of control? A Luddite Planet?</span><hr size=1> The Atom Conspiracy was more a prediction than a novel. Look at the World now. If not for coinciding recent events in our favour we would now be firmly on the path of a Druid society such as that described. Nuclear research has been all but banned for decades but now there is light at the end of the tunnel. Thanks to a pro-nuclear US administration and a need to counter the greenhouse effect. <br>
The Atom Conspiracy, an attempt to reinvent nuclear technology, is ironically what many nations including Iraq are now doing. Just as in the novel, these rebellious states are now labelled as evil. Perhaps they are. The propaganda is rather compelling. I just can't help but notice a similarity between their actions and those of the heroes in the novel. Any World Dictatorship which suppresses technology is evil in my opinion. That last step to becoming a Dictatorship can go unnoticed.<br>
<br>
The Druid government in the book, was it by any chance the US government in the future?<br>
<br>
The novel 1984 was a story of Communism out of control. I question whether Democracy out of control would be any better. Politics mutates over time and human greed is one of the few constants you can safely extrapolate into any future World Order. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=74.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm6.showNextMessage?topicID=74.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=74.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm6.emailToFriend?topicID=74.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm6.threadControl?topicID=74.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm6.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=74.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm6.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=74.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub97.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="nuclearspacefrm4">Nuclear Power in Space<option value="nuclearsp